{#
 # Inline-add button rendered next to EntityType autocomplete fields.
 #
 # The `admin-inline-add` Stimulus controller is attached to the root <span> via
 # {{ attributes.defaults(...) }} rather than a hardcoded data-controller attribute.
 # This is the standard Symfony UX TwigComponent mechanism for attaching a
 # controller: ComponentAttributes merges data-controller / data-action values
 # instead of overwriting them, so this component still composes correctly if
 # the calling context ever stacks another controller onto the same element via
 # component()'s second argument. Rendering {{ attributes }} somewhere on the
 # root element is also expected by Symfony UX for every Twig component —
 # omitting it silently drops any attributes forwarded by the caller.
 #
 # The controller:
 #   - opens the <dialog> via showModal() on button click
 #   - listens for the 'admin:inline:entity:saved' browser event dispatched by
 #     K:Admin:EntityType:InlineForm after a successful save
 #   - closes the dialog and auto-selects the new entity in the Tom Select widget
 #
 # Dialog styling comes entirely from the active CSS theme's dialog()/
 # dialog_header()/dialog_title()/dialog_body() macros (see
 # templates/theme/bootstrap.html.twig or tailwind.html.twig) — no custom CSS
 # ships with this template.
 #
 # ## Shadcn dialog adaptation
 # Replace the <dialog> block below with your shadcn Dialog component.
 # The button (trigger) and the component() call can remain as-is. Keep the
 # {{ attributes.defaults(...) }} call on whichever element should carry the
 # `admin-inline-add` controller in your replacement markup.
 # Your shadcn dialog must close when 'admin:inline:entity:saved' fires on window
 # with a matching entityClass. See docs/INLINE_ADD.md for the full example.
 #
 # Variables (from EntityTypeAddButton PHP component):
 # @var bool               canCreate         - whether the current user has ADMIN_NEW permission
 # @var string             targetEntityClass - FQCN of the entity to create (e.g. App\Entity\Category)
 # @var string             fieldName         - HTML name of the parent select field (e.g. order[category])
 # @var string             entityLabel       - Human-readable label (from #[Admin(label:)] or short class name)
 # @var string             formTypeClass     - Form type class to use in the dialog
 # @var ComponentAttributes attributes       - Standard Twig Component attribute bag; carries the
 #                                             Stimulus controller bindings (see note above)
 #}
{% import kachnitel_admin_theme as css %}

{% if canCreate %}
{#
  Unique dialog id derived from the field name so multiple inline-add dialogs
  on the same page (for different fields) never share the same id attribute.
  We strip brackets so the id is valid HTML: "order[category]" → "order-category".
#}
{% set dialogId = 'inline-add-dialog-' ~ fieldName|replace({'[': '-', ']': '', '.': '-'}) %}

<span {{ attributes.defaults({
  'data-controller': 'admin-inline-add',
  'data-admin-inline-add-entity-class-value': targetEntityClass,
  'data-admin-inline-add-field-name-value': fieldName,
  'data-admin-inline-add-dialog-id-value': dialogId,
}) }}>

  <button type="button"
          class="{{ css.btn_outline_secondary() }} {{ css.btn_sm() }}"
          data-action="admin-inline-add#open"
          aria-haspopup="dialog"
          aria-controls="{{ dialogId }}"
          title="{{ 'Add new'|trans }} {{ entityLabel }}">
    <span aria-hidden="true">+</span>
    {{ entityLabel }}
  </button>

  {#
    ── Native <dialog> implementation ─────────────────────────────────────────
    Works without any CSS framework beyond the active theme's macros (Bootstrap
    or Tailwind). The browser's ::backdrop pseudo-element provides the overlay
    dimming using its own UA default — see the dialog() macro's docblock in
    templates/theme/*.html.twig for how to customise it from your own app CSS.

    To swap for a shadcn dialog, remove this <dialog> element, then wrap the
    component() call in your shadcn <twig:ui:Dialog>.
    See docs/INLINE_ADD.md → "Using the Shadcn Dialog".
  #}
  <dialog id="{{ dialogId }}"
          data-admin-inline-add-target="dialog"
          class="{{ css.dialog() }}"
          aria-labelledby="{{ dialogId }}-title"
          aria-modal="true">

    <div class="{{ css.dialog_header() }}">
      <span id="{{ dialogId }}-title" class="{{ css.dialog_title() }}">
        {{ 'Add New'|trans }} {{ entityLabel }}
      </span>
      <button type="button"
              class="{{ css.btn_close() }}"
              data-action="admin-inline-add#close">
        {{ 'Close'|trans }}
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="{{ css.dialog_body() }}">
      {{ component('K:Admin:EntityType:InlineForm', {
        entityClass: targetEntityClass,
        formTypeClass: formTypeClass,
      }) }}
    </div>

  </dialog>

</span>

{% endif %}
